verses.roman:
ei saba grantha kaila gosāñi sanātana
rūpa-gosāñi kaila yata, ke karu gaṇana

synonyms: ei saba—all these; grantha—scriptures; kaila—compiled; gosāñi sanātana—Sanātana Gosvāmī; rūpa-gosāñi—Rūpa Gosvāmī; kaila—did; yata—all; ke—who; karu gaṇana—can count.
translation: We have already given the names of four books compiled by Sanātana Gosvāmī. Similarly, Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī has also compiled many books, which no one can even count.
